Beginning Monday, March 23rd, the Howard School District will implement alternative teaching methods through March 27th (or until school resumes as directed by the Governor).

Grades 4- 12 will use online instruction and Grades K-3 will begin with packet instruction. Teachers are finalizing their instructional plans this week and will be in communication with parents and students.

We understand that this will be new to most students and parents, but our teachers and staff are committed to working with you to provide the best learning experience possible.

We are operating in unprecedented times but are still committed to your students learning and are available to answer any questions you may have. For questions related to Kindergarten through 6th grade, please call the Elementary School at 772-4443. For Junior High and High School questions, please call the High School at 772-5515.

With the uncertain length of the required school closure by Governor Noem, all students in the elementary and high school buildings must pick up their textbooks, workbooks and personal items either today from 3 to 7pm or tomorrow morning from 8am to 1pm.

For high school students this may include your laptop. Again, all students must pick up items including books, folders, workbooks, and personal items today from 3-7pm or tomorrow morning from 8am to 1pm.

Elementary 3rd Quarter report cards will also be available at this time.

After 1 pm tomorrow, Tuesday March 17th, all Howard District buildings will be locked to begin the deep cleaning process.

If you have questions for the High School please call 772-5515. If you have questions for the Elementary School please call 772-4443.

Thank you for your patience and understanding of this process. Our student’s health and safety is our highest priority, so we appreciate your tolerance as we take steps to sterilize our buildings. Thank you.

The high school/junior high will be open today, Friday, March 13th, from 3:00 - 6:00 pm for any students who wish to collect personal effects, laptop and school materials as a result of Governor Noem's school closure for the coming week. Students are to use the east entrance.

Students who are dual credit/distance education students are strongly advised to make certain that they have all necessary materials to stay current with their distance courses as we anticipate these courses will continue by these off-site providers. At this time, all other courses are suspended until further notice.

As well, the superintendent's office will continue to supply the communities of our district with information as this situation progresses.

Other requests for access to the school to collect materials will be handled on a case-by-case basis. Students are encouraged to check their emails throughout the week as well as access the school webpage for developing information.

post_text:
Press Release- For Immediate Release

At the request of Governor Noem, the remainder of the SDHSAA Class B Girls Basketball tournament is postponed. In addition, all SDHSAA state basketball tournaments for next weekend, along with the Visual Arts competition, are also postponed. The Student Council Convention, all Region music contests, and All-State Band scheduled for later this month are cancelled.

This is a difficult decision and comes amid constant conversation and information sharing between the SDHSAA, the Governor’s Office, and the Department of Health. We will evaluate the future of the postponed events in concert with those same entities. The safety of everyone involved is our foremost concern, followed by exploring all options to provide the student-athlete with the opportunity to finish their season.

We thank everyone for their patience and understanding in a very difficult time, and we apologize for any inconvenience that this may cause.

Dan Swartos, SDHSAA Executive Director

post_text:
Feed Information for BB Double Header at Emery:

Bridgewater-Emery FCCLA will once again be hosting the 3rd Annual Soup Supper in the Multi at Emery from 5:00-7:45pm on Thursday, January 23rd, as we host the doubleheader basketball game against Howard. There will be a variety of soups to sample and enjoy. The event is a free-will offering and will support the Bridgewater-Emery FCCLA chapter’s activities.

FCCLA will also host a collection drive for the Bridgewater Food Pantry during the soup supper. We encourage community members and students to bring the below items, which will be donated to the food pantry. Please limit donations to only unused/unopened:

Paper Products (Kleenex, paper towel or toilet paper)
Dish Soap
Laundry Soap

FCCLA and the Bridgewater Food Pantry thank you.

National Honor Society, in conjunction with Horizon Health Care’s TSU2C, is sponsoring its 3rd annual “Hat Day”.

On Friday, Oct. 11th, students and employees of participating businesses may wear a hat to work/school if he/she has purchased a sticker for $1.00.

Last year, NHS raised $341 for Miner County cancer patients, and we are hoping to surpass our last year’s donation.

If you aren't a hat person, you may still purchase a sticker and place the sticker on your shirt to show your support.

Stickers available at both the elementary and high school, River's Edge Bank, and Horizon Foundation.

post_text:
The Howard District has many outstanding teachers and classified staff professionals.

We are asking for your assistance in identifying those individuals whose skills, dedication, understanding and caring for children have made a positive impact on the lives of our students, and whose service has truly been outstanding in its contribution to the overall educational climate of the district.

▪️Who can be nominated?
Any full time employee who has an active contract or certification. This nominee must have served with the school district for at least one school year.
▪️Teacher of the Year Nominees can be:
-teachers
-librarians
-SPED teachers
▪️Classified Nominees can be:
-secretarial staff
-paraprofessionals
-custodial staff

One staff member from each building and one classified staff member will be chosen each year.

To nominate a teacher or classified staff member, please follow this link and find the Nomination Form:

https://howard.k12.sd.us/DistrictResouces.html

Forms will be available on the site 3/11/19

The Show is still scheduled to go on! Set up of booths has begun--if you are able to help out, tables, chairs and booths will be going up this afternoon through about 6 pm--stop by if you can offer some assistance.

In addition--get those exhibits together!! Bake some cookies or find those crafts or photos you've completed this past year! Farmers--we have lot areas for small grain, corn, silage as well as vegetables you stored away last harvest! Prize money is awarded to the 1st, 2nd and 3rd place in each exhibit area as well as a $50 sweepstakes to the overall exhibitor in the areas of Crops - Foods/Canning - Crafts - Photography!

Exhibits are due to the Howard Armory by 12 noon on Thursday, February 7. Pick up items by 6 pm.

Be a part of this annual event!
